in the developed world where FDI flows all the time. This \r\npaper explores whether terrorism reduces FDI inflows, and argues that foreign investors adjust their information by observing whether the host country has the capability to deal with terrorism. Foreign aid from the United States that is used \r\nspecifically for counterterrorism is a good signal of counterterrorism potential. Using two commonly used terrorism datasets and drawing upon a time-series cross-sectional data analysis, this paper finds that while terrorism plays a role of an obstacle to FDI inflows, countries that receive more counterterrorism aid are less vulnerable to this adverse effect. It also shows that conflict-tied aid has a similar mitigating effect for terrorism's negative impact on FDI. "}}]},{"typeName":"subject","multiple":true,"typeClass":"controlledVocabulary","value":["Social Sciences"]},{"typeName":"depositor","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"Replication, FPA"},{"typeName":"dateOfDeposit","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"2016-02-26"}]}},"files":[{"label":"FPA_terrorism&FDI_data.tab","restricted":false,"version":2,"datasetVersionId":79910,"dataFile":{"id":2788684,"persistentId":"doi:10.7910/DVN/BV7YUU/ZK3RC5","pidURL":"https://doi.org/10.7910/DVN/BV7YUU/ZK3RC5","filename":"FPA_terrorism&FDI_data.tab","contentType":"text/tab-separated-values","filesize":841540,"storageIdentifier":"s3://dvn-cloud:1531cc39b08-781793af82bf","originalFileFormat":"text/csv","originalFormatLabel":"Comma Separated Values","UNF":"UNF:6:EeQ0qsVt5A6OcEL0+T/S0Q==","rootDataFileId":-1,"md5":"d93557f7e7d40e63fd381d2b36f3f5c0","checksum":{"type":"MD5","value":"d93557f7e7d40e63fd381d2b36f3f5c0"}}},{"label":"Rcode_terrorism&FDI.R","restricted":false,"version":1,"datasetVersionId":79910,"dataFile":{"id":2788683,"persistentId":"doi:10.7910/DVN/BV7YUU/YXDNDT","pidURL":"https://doi.org/10.7910/DVN/BV7YUU/YXDNDT","filename":"Rcode_terrorism&FDI.R","contentType":"type/x-r-syntax","file